            <thetext>This bug does affect Firefox and Opera.

Steps to reproduce:

1) Create a command with the shortcut &quot;Ctrl+W&quot;
2) Assign it to a button
3) Hit the shortcut key

Hitting the shortcut keys once or with a short pause is no problem. Holding the shortcut keys leads Firefox to close the tab/window.

It seems that there are events which aren&#39;t properly stopped.</thetext>
